  <h2 class="section-title">Specialty Picks</h2>
  <div class="table-container">
    <table class="rec-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Item</th>
          <th>Category</th>
          <th>Price</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
          <th>Players</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {specialty.map(s => {
          const playerCount = getPlayerCount(s.name);
          return (
            <tr>
              <td class="headset-name">{s.name}</td>
              <td>{s.category}</td>
              <td><span class={priceBadgeClass(s.price)}>{s.price}</span></td>
              <td class="notes">{s.notes}</td>
              <td class="center players">
                {playerCount > 0 ? (
                  <div class="usage-wrapper">
                    <span class="usage-count">{playerCount}</span>
                    <div class="player-dropdown">
                      {getPlayersForHeadset(s.name).map(p => (
                        <a href={`${base}players/${p.id}/`}>{p.data.name}</a>
                      ))}
                    </div>
                  </div>
                ) : '—'}
              </td>
            </tr>
          );
        })}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="info-sections">
    <h2 class="section-title">Arena Shooter Audio Principles</h2>
    <p>Arena shooters like Quake Live, Diabotical, and Reflex Arena rely on precise stereo imaging rather than cinematic sound design. The key audio priorities are:</p>
    <div class="table-container">
      <table class="rec-table info-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Attribute</th>
            <th>Importance</th>
            <th>Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Imaging</td><td>Critical</td><td class="notes">Accurate left/right/front directional awareness</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Frequency balance</td><td>High</td><td class="notes">Excess bass masks footsteps and item sounds</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Soundstage</td><td>Secondary</td><td class="notes">Helpful but less important than directional precision</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Comfort</td><td>High</td><td class="notes">Long sessions require lightweight headphones</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>Open-back headphones are generally preferred — they provide clearer spatial cues and less bass masking than closed-back designs.</p>

    <h2 class="section-title">How Arena Shooter Audio Works</h2>
    <p>Arena shooters use clean stereo positional audio with no cinematic mixing. This means:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Stereo audio works best</li>
      <li>Virtual surround processing is rarely helpful and can reduce directional accuracy</li>
      <li>Neutral tuning improves clarity of movement cues</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="section-title">Microphone Options</h2>
    <p>Many recommended headphones here are not headsets and require a separate microphone. Common solutions:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Antlion ModMic (attaches to any headphone)</li>
      <li>V-MODA BoomPro (works with headphones that have a 3.5mm input)</li>
      <li>USB desk microphone (e.g. Blue Yeti, HyperX QuadCast)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="section-title">EQ Guidance (Optional)</h2>
    <p>EQ is optional but can improve competitive clarity. Apply carefully:</p>
    <div class="table-container">
      <table class="rec-table info-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Frequency</th>
            <th>Adjustment</th>
            <th>Reason</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">60–150 Hz</td><td>Slight cut</td><td class="notes">Reduces bass masking of footsteps</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">2–4 kHz</td><td>Slight boost</td><td class="notes">Improves footstep clarity</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">6–8 kHz</td><td>Small boost</td><td class="notes">Sharpens positional cues</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>Use Equalizer APO (Windows) with Peace GUI, or ReaEQ. Oratory1990's presets on Reddit are a good starting point for many headphones.</p>

    <h2 class="section-title">Community Reference — Mad Lust Envy Gaming Guide</h2>
    <blockquote>
      The long-running Mad Lust Envy Headphone Gaming Guide (Head-Fi) is one of the most widely referenced community resources for gaming audio. Several headphones on this page also appear in that guide. Note that guide covers general gaming broadly; this page focuses specifically on arena shooters.
    </blockquote>
    <div class="table-container">
      <table class="rec-table info-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Headphone</th>
            <th>MLE's reason for inclusion</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Audio-Technica AD700X</td><td class="notes">Long-standing budget competitive king for positional imaging</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">AKG K702</td><td class="notes">Very wide soundstage, strong positional accuracy</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Sennheiser PC38X</td><td class="notes">Called "audiophile level" — top headset pick</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Beyerdynamic DT880/DT990</td><td class="notes">B-tier staples for competitive FPS</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="section-title">Common Mistakes</h2>
    <div class="table-container">
      <table class="rec-table info-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Mistake</th>
            <th>Result</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Choosing bass-heavy gaming headsets</td><td class="notes">Footsteps become harder to hear</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Enabling virtual surround processing</td><td class="notes">Can reduce directional accuracy in arena shooters</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Using high-impedance headphones without an amp</td><td class="notes">Weak output, reduced clarity</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="headset-name">Buying a headset with a built-in mic when a better open-back option exists</td><td class="notes">Worse imaging for no real benefit</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="section-title">Quick Decision Guide</h2>
    <div class="decision-guide">
      <p><strong>Need isolation (LAN/office)?</strong></p>
      <p>→ Yes: Closed-back — Beyerdynamic DT770 or Audeze Maxwell</p>
      <p>→ No: Open-back — start here</p>

      <p><strong>Want plug-and-play with no amp?</strong></p>
      <p>→ Yes: Sennheiser HD560S</p>
      <p>→ No: Beyerdynamic DT880 with a DAC/AMP like the Fosi K7</p>

      <p><strong>Need a built-in mic?</strong></p>
      <p>→ Yes: Drop EPOS PC38X</p>
      <p>→ No: Any open-back headphone + Antlion ModMic</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="back-link">
    <a href={`${base}recommendations/`}>← Back to Recommendations</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .reviewer-legend {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary, #12121a);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .legend-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  .badge.gt { background: #4a9eff; color: #fff; }
  .badge.bs { background: #ff6b6b; color: #fff; }
  .badge.jv { background: #6bcb77; color: #000; }
  .badge.asr { background: #facc15; color: #000; }
  .badge.mle { background: #c084fc; color: #fff; }

  .price-legend {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary, #888);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .price-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.125rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-family: monospace;
  }

  .price-budget { background: #22c55e; color: #000; }
  .price-mid { background: #3b82f6; color: #fff; }
  .price-premium { background: #f97316; color: #fff; }
  .price-legendary { background: #ef4444; color: #fff; }

  .section-title {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-primary, #fff);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color, #2a2a3a);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .table-container {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .rec-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
  }

  .rec-table th,
  .rec-table td {
    padding: 0.75rem;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color, #2a2a3a);
  }

  .rec-table th {
    background: var(--bg-secondary, #12121a);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-secondary, #888);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }

  .rec-table th[title] {
    cursor: help;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-style: dotted;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .rec-table tbody tr:hover {
    background: var(--bg-secondary, #12121a);
  }

  .headset-name {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary, #fff);
  }

